;s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1310:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/various-features-and-benefits-of-the-mongodb-database-framework/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/database-1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"Various Features and Benefits of the MongoDB Database Framework\" alt=\"Various Features and Benefits of the MongoDB Database Framework\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">Database management is a huge concern for everyone, as data is regarded as an asset in today&#8217;s time. Not just efficiently storing data, it is equally important to look after the security and confidentiality of data. Once data is gone to wrong hands, it will be misused, and the organization may have to face dire [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/various-features-and-benefits-of-the-mongodb-database-framework/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Walter Moore\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7723:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/various-features-and-benefits-of-the-mongodb-database-framework/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/database-1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"Various Features and Benefits of the MongoDB Database Framework\" alt=\"Various Features and Benefits of the MongoDB Database Framework\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p>Database management is a huge concern for\neveryone, as data is regarded as an asset in today&#8217;s time. Not just efficiently\nstoring data, it is equally important to look after the security and confidentiality\nof data. Once data is gone to wrong hands, it will be misused, and the\norganization may have to face dire consequences. For database management with\noptimum security, MongoDB platform is quite popularly used. But, the question\nis why people should choose MongoDB? What are the benefits of using this\ndatabase framework? Answers of all these questions will be discussed in the\nfollowing section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The benefits of MongoDB will be discussed in\nthe following section of this piece of writing. These benefits have been\napproved by the database developers and managers in the professional IT field.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Loaded with\nArrays of Features</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The main reason to love MongoDB as database\nframework is that the framework is poised with a large number of features. All\nthese features will make the database management process seamless and simple.\nFor the beginners or novice people, it has to be stated that MongoDB is a NoSQL\ndatabase. In 2019, the global trend is to opt for a NoSQL database, as it will\nprovide more convenience. Nevertheless, it ensures better security for the data\nstored on the database server. In the following section, the highlighted\nfeatures of MongoDB will be discussed.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>MongoDB is known\nfor being the aggression framework, which is particularly good for the database\nmanagers these days.</li><li>BSON format makes\nthis framework more useful and effective.</li><li>Ad-Hoc query\nenables seamless data management.</li><li>File storage and\nindexing are also highlighted features of MongoDB.</li><li>Replication of\ndata for data backup is easy with MongoDB.</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Easy and\nEffective Load Balancing</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The MongoDB database platform is known for its\nload balancing feature. When you have to manage a large set of data, load\nbalancing will automatically emerge as an important factor. Managing large size\ndata on the database framework is often troublesome when SQL based database\nframework is used. If you choose a NoSQL based database framework, this problem\ncan be overcome with precision. With MongoDB, effective load balancing will\ntake place. It will ensure that your database does not face any sorts of\nproblems in sorting data or processing data. Overload can cause database server\nglitches and unexpected errors associated with slowness in processing data.\nThanks to MongoDB, the database managers do not have to face all these issues\nat all.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Shrading of\nthe Data</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Horizontal scaling of the data can be done\nwith shrading. With a relational database, this feature will be found\nunavailable. You can only get this feature when you use MongoDB. So, what this\nfeature is all about? How can it help? Well, it can distribute the data across\ndifferent machines. This is why this feature is important, as well as required.\nWith shrading, the process of managing database will turn easier. It will help\nin the faster data processing. As a result, sorting data will be simpler and\nnot time-consuming. It is frustrating to give a lot of time to the database in\nsearching for the data. With the use of MongoDB, this problem can be avoided\ndue to the shrading facility.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Speed of the\nMongoDB</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The speed of MongoDB is also commendable, and\nthat is why modern database managers prefer using this database platform. It\ncomes with advanced speed and support for the users. Sorting data and searching\ndata on the database will take minimal time. It is more time effective than the\ndatabase platforms which are SQL based. Another notable thing is editing or\nmodifying data will happen without any glitches. Data will not take a long time\nto be saved. For backup, data copying speed is also quite good.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Ad-Hoc\nQueries of MongoDB</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With MongoDB, users will get the facility for\ncompatibility with wide ranges of queries, different types of searches, and\nregular expressions. The queries will include the user-defined JavaScript\nfunctions. Having introduced unique query language, the MongoDB comes with\nad-hoc query support in offering for the users. The ad-hoc query works on the\nindexing of the BSON documents. Overall, the ad-hoc query feature gives more\nfreedom to the database managers to manage the data more logically or\npractically. The differences between SQL Select query and resembling query are\ndiscussed in the following section.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Schema-Less\nDatabase Framework</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Schema-less database framework is another\nhighlight of this type of database. With MongoDB, this is another significant\nbenefit that you can enjoy. This database framework is written upon the C++\nprogramming language. Due to this reason, managing as well as using this\ndatabase will become simpler. With its simplicity, the database can be managed\nwith perfection. So, for the modern developers as well as database managers,\nthe MongoDB is always a good thing. It provides amazing ranges of benefits in\noffering.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Arrays of\nCapped Collections</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>With MongoDB, the capped collection has been\nsupported. It is to be noted that the database framework has a fixed size of\ncollections within the database. This database has to maintain the insertion\norder for its collections. As soon as the limit has been reached, the database\nframework will start behaving like a circular queue. So, in this way, sorting\nand managing the data on the database will turn simpler. Overall, database\nmanagement will become a seamless experience.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Flawless\nData Indexing Support</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Data indexing is another benefit of the\nMongoDB database framework, as it ensures the improvement of the performance of\nthe search indexes that are created. Any documents on the database server can\nbe index if you are using the MongoDB database framework. It is advanced and\nseamless. It comes with effective database support in offering for the users.\n\nOverall, this database management framework has\na lot of unique and effective ranges of benefits. These advantages are crucial\nto be understood for the database managers. This is the reason why you need to\nchoose a professional and powerful database management tool.&nbsp; From all these aspects and considerations,\nthe MongoDB database framework is always a leading database management\nframework.<a href=\"http://www.remotedba.com/why-remote-dba/\">With\nRemoteDBA.com</a>,\nyou can get the best database services possible for your business.\n\n\n\n</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/various-features-and-benefits-of-the-mongodb-database-framework/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/various-features-and-benefits-of-the-mongodb-database-framework/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"How to create a memorable brand\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 20 Jun 2019 00:39:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Introducing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://oceanwp.org/?p=479132\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1187:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/brainstorming-branding-busines1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"How to create a memorable brand\" alt=\"How to create a memorable brand\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">When people think about creating a brand, the majority thinks about designing a logo. This is indeed an important part of the process, yet a logo doesn’t make a brand. Even your company is not a brand. What is then? All the people who work in your business, their attitudes and ideas drive the brand. [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Linda Cartwright\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12472:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/brainstorming-branding-busines1.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"How to create a memorable brand\" alt=\"How to create a memorable brand\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\">\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/advertising-brand-branding-1449081-3-1024x602.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-479138\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/advertising-brand-branding-1449081-3-1024x602.jpg 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/advertising-brand-branding-1449081-3-300x176.jpg 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/advertising-brand-branding-1449081-3-768x451.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When people\nthink about creating a brand, the majority thinks about designing a logo. This\nis indeed an important part of the process, yet a logo doesn’t make a brand.\nEven your company is not a brand. What is then?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>All the\npeople who work in your business, their attitudes and ideas drive the brand. The\nway your staff interacts with your customers, customer journey and experience\nwith your product creates your brand. The visual components of brand identity\n(colors + logo) and the packaging create an impression of your brand. Your\nbrand’s tone of voice, the message in its slogan, and the way you display\ncontent on your website and social media represent your brand. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Everything\ntogether is your brand – it’s a <strong>personality</strong>\nof your business and its <strong>promise</strong> to\nyour customers. You cannot split those elements – they are organically\ninterwoven. Instead, when you create your brand from scratch, think of them as\nof different focal points of one process.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Who you are?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Before you\nstart working on any of the elements below you must find out who you are as a\nbusiness. I know, easier said than done. It makes sense to <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/agency/market-research-tools-resources\">conduct market research</a>. Before you start shaping your\nidentity, you must know who your <strong>audience</strong>\nis, who your <strong>competition</strong> is and what\n<strong>value</strong> you can offer to your\ncustomers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Knowing\nyour audience is the first step. You cannot target pre-teens and working\nparents with the same message (at least, it’s not likely). Knowing your\ncompetition is essential to finding out what needs of your audience aren’t yet\naddressed. Your values, on the other hand, is the answer to those needs. What\ndo you represent? What do you stand for? What is the purpose of your existence?\n(apart from making money that is). What only you can offer to your customers?\nWhy should they choose you? What makes you different from your competitors? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you\nanswer all those questions, you are ready to tell the <strong>story</strong> of your brand. People like stories and remember them. The\nmost successful brand stories follow the pattern: problem – solution – success.\nThat is, a problem existed, the solution was offered thus laying the foundation\nfor the brand and brand’s prosperity. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Create a personality</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With all\nthe data about audience and values on your hands, you can start creating a\npersonality for your brand. Before you will dive in design particulars, such as\ncolors, type, and logo, decide upon the qualities you will convey through them.\nLook at some key points. Remember, each <strong>quality</strong>\ncan be viewed as <strong>positive</strong>. The\nimportant thing is what describes your brand best and what will best appeal to\nyour audience.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Are\nyou lightning-fast or slow, careful and meticulous? </li><li>Are\nyou serious and reliable or fun and carefree?</li><li>Are\nyou traditional or cutting-edge?</li><li>Are\nyou old and experienced or youthful and fresh?</li><li>Are\nyou affordable or ritzy?</li><li>Are\nyou family-friendly or provocative? </li><li>Are\nyou everyday or special-occasion? </li><li>Are\nyou ubiquitous or out-of-the-ordinary?</li><li>Are\nyou careful or daring? </li><li>Are\nyou factual or opinionated?</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And so on –\ncontinue until you have a very clear idea about your brand’s personality. Every\ndetail is important because that is where you will be coming from while working\non your brand’s name, visual identity, and tone of voice.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/camera-coffee-composition-1509428-2-1024x668.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-479139\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/camera-coffee-composition-1509428-2-1024x668.jpg 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/camera-coffee-composition-1509428-2-300x196.jpg 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/camera-coffee-composition-1509428-2-768x501.jpg 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/camera-coffee-composition-1509428-2.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Brand name</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>When you\nhave decided on <strong>key characteristics</strong>,\nuse mind-mapping to cluster them in semantic blocks of related <strong>keywords</strong>. You can jot down associations\nthey evoke, moods, connotations, and objects you visualize whey you think of\nabstract qualities. Don’t be afraid to step away from dictionary synonyms and\nuse your own experience. Many personal associations you think are unique to you\nmay turn out to be universal. This approach is useful because it helps to\nelicit vivid symbols that speak volumes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>A physical <strong>object</strong> representing an abstract <strong>idea</strong> (a sprout or a leaf for growth, elephant for long memory, a paperclip for saving and ordering, a bull for power and energy, a jaguar for speed) is a shortcut into the imagination of your audience and a great way to convey ideas. For example, companies that offer <a href=\"https://www.paperhelp.org/\">help with writing papers</a> often use word “paper” in their brand name. That’s not only because the word is used to signify any written assignment as opposed to other types of projects. Paper is a physical object one can interact with, it conjures sensory and motor experiences (rustling of pages, the smell of pen or print ink, feeling of textures, a memory of handwriting or thumbing through a book) and it creates an immediate emotional response – and therefore is more memorable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Still, it’s\njust one of many possible approaches to coming up with a name for your brand.\nOther popular name types are <strong>eponymous</strong>\n(after a founder or prominent figure: <em>Disney,\nTesla, Proctor &amp; Gamble, Dr. Martens</em>), <strong>descriptive</strong> (telling upfront what company does: <em>Great Western Railways, American Airlines,\nBooking.com</em>), <strong>acronymic</strong> (<em>KFC </em>for <em>Kentucky Fried Chicken, DHL </em>for <em>Dalsey,\nHillblom and Lynn, LG for Lucky-Goldstar</em>), <strong>suggestive</strong> (dictionary words, slightly altered words, or both used\nin combination to describe key attributes: <em>Facebook,\nSnapchat, Rayban, PayPal, Slack, Lyft, Kleenex</em>), and <strong>abstract</strong> (with no intrinsic meaning, often <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Onomatopoeia\">onomatopœic</a>, like <em>Rolex, Kodak</em>, <em>Tic Tac</em>).</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Visual identity</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>With brand personality\nand name ready, it’s time to choose your <strong>colors</strong>.\nThey are a powerful tool to get your message across because they are strongly\nassociated with different <strong>feelings</strong>.\nAbout 85 percent of consumers cite color is a primary reason to choose a\nproduct, so this is an uber-important decision to make.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To pick the\ncolor that is most suitable for your brand, you may want to do some research.\nGo through the <a href=\"https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2010/01/color-theory-for-designers-part-1-the-meaning-of-color/\">psychology of color guides</a> and look at some <a href=\"https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/psychology-of-color\">examples of existing companies</a>. Pay close attention to brands\nwithin your industry – it’s important to decide whether you want to compete in\none league with them or stand out from the crowd.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Another\ngreat way to come up with the color that will represent your brand best is\ncreating a mood board, either digital or physical, to get the most generalized feeling\nof your brand’s identity, ideally summed up in <strong>one key motif</strong>. You are not limited to one color, but often less is\nmore. About 95 percent of the top brand logos use one, or\nat most, two colors.\nToo many can dilute the message you intend to convey. Unless your message is\ndiversity, versatility, and wide choice, of course (cue <em>Instagram, Google, Microsoft, eBay</em>). </p>\n\n\n\n<p>With name\nand colors, you are all set to create a logotype. Unfortunately, there is no\nuniversal recipe. Simple shapes tend to be more memorable (think <em>Apple,</em> <em>Nike, MasterCard</em>), but there always be exceptions (<em>Starbucks, Unilever, Warner Brothers,\nHeineken</em>).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>However, logos\nthat are open to interpretation and have multiple meanings (<em>Pexels, Airbnb</em>) are more likely to be\nremembered because they act as brainteasers and catch the eye. Many successful\nlogos feature a wordmark or initials in such way as to create a shape and\nconveys additional meaning (arrow in <em>FedEx</em>,\nheadphones in <em>Beats Electronics</em>, A to\nZ in <em>Amazon</em>, P representing a pin in <em>Pinterest</em>).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/andrew-ridley-76547-unsplash-1-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-479140\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/andrew-ridley-76547-unsplash-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/andrew-ridley-76547-unsplash-1-300x225.jpg 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/andrew-ridley-76547-unsplash-1-768x576.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Brand’s tone of voice</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Now is the\ntime to give your brand a voice. To do it, try to imagine your brand as a\nperson with all the qualities you brainstormed above (see “Who you are?”\nparagraph). If something is missing, fill in the gaps, noting every detail.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now imagine\nseveral scenarios, for example:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>A\ncustomer wrote an angry Twit/Facebook post – how would you react?</li><li>A\ncustomer leaves a five-star review – how would you respond?</li><li>A\ncustomer approaches you with concern – how do you want them to feel when the\nissue is resolved?</li><li>A\nnon-profit approaches you seeking sponsorship for a charity event – what would\nyou say and which words would you choose?</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>And so on –\ncome up with your own best- and worst-case scenarios. After you are done\nanswering, revise your answers. Are you happy with them? Is this how your brand\nshould sound like? If so, what are the key values these answers communicate?\n(Friendliness and approachability? Competence and reassurance?) </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Are your\nemployees aware of these values? Would they respond to the above situations the\nway you imagine? Remember, that the key to a memorable brand is consistency.\nYour voice should sound uniform across platforms, media, and all areas of your\nbusiness.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Creating a\nmemorable brand doesn’t necessarily take a lot of money. It is quite possible\non a small budget (everyone knows a story of Nike’s iconic swoosh purchased for\n$35 from a college student). However, you must make sure that everything in\nyour brand’s identity reflects your core values and is consistent with your\nmission. </p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-create-a-memorable-brand/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:25:\"https://oceanwp.org/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"\n	hourly	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"\n	1	\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:18:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Thu, 11 Jul 2019 11:14:31 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34: