nce.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"3-samsung-galaxy-s10\">3. Samsung Galaxy S10</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":204} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/61YVqHdFRxL._SX569_.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-204\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A top Android phone, overshadowed by its big brother</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date: </strong>March 2019 | <strong>Weight: </strong>157g | <strong>Dimensions: </strong>149.9 x 70.4 x 7.8mm | <strong>OS: </strong>Android 9 | <strong>Screen size: </strong>6.1-inch | <strong>Resolution: </strong>1440 x 3040 | <strong>CPU: </strong>Snapdragon 855 / Exynos 9820 | <strong>RAM: </strong>8GB | <strong>Storage: </strong>128/512GB | <strong>Battery: </strong>3,400mAh | <strong>Rear camera: </strong>12MP + 12MP + 16MP | <strong>Front camera: </strong>10MP</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Great screen-to-body ratioWireless PowerShare perkS10 Plus is betterBixby button not needed</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s close at the top, with Huawei snapping at Samsung\'s heels it\'s never been tougher for the South Korean firm, but the Galaxy S10 still manages to muscle its way into number three spot.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bigger S10 Plus is by far Samsung\'s best phone, but the standard S10 backs almost all the same top-end features into a more compact form factor and slightly lower price tag (but still steep).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy S10 gets proper under-the-hood upgrades. You’ll like all of these powerful features, while your friends will like the new Wireless PowerShare perk – it helps them out more than you. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"4-huawei-mate-20-pro\">4. Huawei Mate 20 Pro</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":205} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/huawei-mate-20-proheader.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-205\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A power-house of an Android phone</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date: </strong>November 2018 | <strong>Weight: </strong>189g | <strong>Dimensions: </strong>157.8 x 72.3 x 8.6mm | <strong>OS: </strong>Android 9 | <strong>Screen size: </strong>6.39-inch | <strong>Resolution: </strong>1440 x 3120 | <strong>CPU: </strong>Kirin 980 | <strong>RAM: </strong>8GB | <strong>Storage: </strong>256GB | <strong>Battery: </strong>4200mAh | <strong>Rear camera: </strong>40MP + 20MP + 8MP | <strong>Front camera: </strong>24MP</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In-screen fingerprint scannerGreat triple camerasThe UI needs refinementHigh price</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Huawei Mate 20 Pro offers up a heady mix of design, power and performance with a party piece in the form of an in-display fingerprint scanner thrown in too.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Mate 20 Pro packs a huge 6.39-inch display giving you a lots of space for gaming and movies, and its QHD resolution and HDR10 support ensures everything looks great.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It also comes with three rear cameras, nabbing the excellent 40MP wide-angle and 8MP telephoto lenses from the P20 Pro - but the third sensor is new. It\'s an ultra-wide 16MP snapper allowing you to cram even more of your surroundings into each shot.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Mate 20 Pro is a full-featured phone for a full-featured price - it even has a few tricks you won’t see elsewhere, and more powerful specs than most of its competitors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"5-samsung-galaxy-note-9\">5. Samsung Galaxy Note 9</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":206} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Samsung-Galaxy-Note-9-Official-600x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-206\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the highest-spec phones on the market</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date: </strong>August 2018 | <strong>Weight: </strong>205g | <strong>Dimensions: </strong>162 x 76.4 x 9mm | <strong>OS: </strong>Android 8.1 | <strong>Screen size: </strong>6.4-inch | <strong>Resolution: </strong>2960×1440 | <strong>CPU: </strong>Exynos 9810 | <strong>RAM: </strong>6/8GB | <strong>Storage: </strong>128/512GB (up to 1TB with card) | <strong>Battery: </strong>4,000mAh | <strong>Rear camera: </strong>12MP + 12MP | <strong>Front camera: </strong>8MP<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amazon.com/Samsung-Factory-Unlocked-Warranty-Lavender/dp/B07H8PXT7K?psc=1&amp;SubscriptionId=AKIAIPHVZTVH6LZ5BFZA&amp;tag=hawk-future-20&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;camp=2025&amp;creative=165953&amp;creativeASIN=B07H8PXT7K&amp;ascsubtag=trd-custom-tracking-20\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> </strong></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Much better batteryImproved S PenHefty device to holdMostly iterative upgrades</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The South Korean features again with Galaxy Note 9 in at five in our best Android phones lists.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Galaxy Note 9 boasts a huge screen and a huge amount of power under the hood, plus there\'s the iconic S Pen stylus which slides into the body of the phone for safe keeping.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It means the Note 9 offers a huge array of productivity functions few phones can compete with, but the overall package isn\'t quite as finessed as the Galaxy S10 Plus - not to mention its high price tag.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For power users who want a phone that will doing pretty much anything they ask of it, the Galaxy Note 9 is a top choice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '5 best Android phones 2019: which should you buy?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '201-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-26 13:53:51', '2019-06-26 10:53:51', '', 201, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2019/06/26/201-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(210, 1, '2019-06-26 13:56:07', '2019-06-26 10:56:07', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":194} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Huawei-Enjoy-9-specs-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-194\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After&nbsp;Google suspended Huawei\'s future access to Android Play Store&nbsp;and security updates, there are serious question marks over the future of Huawei and Honor phones.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>While Google and Huawei have promised to support phones currently on the market, it\'s not clear how long they\'ll receive Android updates or access to the Google Play Store, which would severely curtail their usefulness compared to the competition.</em> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Huawei is the&nbsp;second biggest smartphone manufacturer in the world&nbsp;after Samsung, and it\'s got there by offering up some excellent devices along the way.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s grown in strength significantly over the past couple of years, to the point that if you\'re looking for the best Huawei phones around, there\'s a wide range to choose from.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the top of the range are the flagship&nbsp;Huawei P30 Pro&nbsp;and&nbsp;Huawei Mate 20 Pro, but our best Huawei phones list also includes great, affordable handsets such as the&nbsp;Huawei P Smart.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That means when it comes to picking the best Huawei phone for you, it can be tricky. With that in mind we’ve highlighted the best Huawei phones the firm currently has to offer and ranked them.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, not everyone’s budget and needs are the same, so just because something is lower in this list it doesn’t mean it will be a worse choice for you than something higher.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And let\'s not forget, Huawei\'s most exciting phone of 2019 is yet to go on sale, with the foldable&nbsp;Huawei Mate X&nbsp;slated to land in stores in the coming months - however, with&nbsp;the recent issues&nbsp;with the&nbsp;Samsung Galaxy Fold&nbsp;it appears all&nbsp;foldable phones&nbsp;are currently on a temporary hold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While Huawei\'s current crop of smartphones are great devices, you now need to take into consideration the long-term future of the handsets and whether or not it\'s worth the risk in investing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'re willing to take the risk, our list will show you at a glance their specs, highlights and main weaknesses, so you can make an informed choice as to which is the best Huawei for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The best Huawei phones of 2019: find your perfect Huawei', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-26 13:56:07', '2019-06-26 10:56:07', '', 193, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2019/06/26/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
