(220, 1, '2019-06-26 14:09:35', '2019-06-26 11:09:35', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":208} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/hKZfp4YKrsG4knsPZZwFch-970-80.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-208\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you\'re on the hunt for the best Android smartphone around, you\'ve come to the right place. We\'ve put all the major Google-powered handsets through their paces to give you our best Android phones round-down.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There\'s one key way in which Android is massively different from its Apple-branded smartphone competition - the number of phones out there running Google\'s hot mobile OS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Update:&nbsp;</strong><em>The OnePlus 7 Pro has been through our rigorous review process, and it now appears in our best Android phone list. Scroll down to see our full verdict on where the latest from OnePlus sits.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The big names are all here. The many variations in screen size, processor power, software features and design makes finding the best Android phone for you extremely tough.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To help find the most fitting Android phone for you, we\'ve rounded up the best Android handsets out there today, rating the phones on hardware performance, OS upgrade potential and, of course, how shiny and nice they are to have and boast about to work colleagues.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So here they are - the best Android phones money can buy today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"1-samsung-galaxy-s10-plus\">1. Samsung Galaxy S10 Plus</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":202} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/2019-03-01-product.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-202\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best Android phone you can buy right now</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date:&nbsp;</strong>March 2019 |&nbsp;<strong>Weight:&nbsp;</strong>175g |&nbsp;<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>157.6 x 74.1 x 7.8mm |&nbsp;<strong>OS:&nbsp;</strong>Android 9 |&nbsp;<strong>Screen size:&nbsp;</strong>6.4-inch |&nbsp;<strong>Resolution:&nbsp;</strong>1440 x 3040 |&nbsp;<strong>CPU:&nbsp;</strong>Snapdragon 855 / Exynos 9820 |&nbsp;<strong>RAM:&nbsp;</strong>8/12GB |&nbsp;<strong>Storage:&nbsp;</strong>128/512GB/1TB |&nbsp;<strong>Battery:&nbsp;</strong>4,100mAh |&nbsp;<strong>Rear camera:&nbsp;</strong>12MP + 12MP + 16MP |&nbsp;<strong>Front camera:&nbsp;</strong>10MP + 8MPT</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>he best smartphone screen around Excellent cameras It\'s not cheap Design offers little grip</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy S10 Plus is the best Android phone you can buy right now, packing the best of what Samsung has to offer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s a big phone that\'s designed for big hands - and it takes the very best of what\'s on the smartphone market and puts it together in a compelling package that we\'ve loved testing.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Super AMOLED 6.4-inch display has been measured as&nbsp;the very best around, with super colours, plus there\'s a fingerprint scanner embedded in the display.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Battery life is an improvement over the S9 Plus, thanks to the larger 4,100mAh battery inside and you also get Samsung\'s new Wireless PowerShare, allowing you to wirelessly charge other devices on the rear of the handset.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The trio of cameras on the rear of the Galaxy S10 Plus are among the best on the market, offering more features, shooting modes and overall clarity.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"2-huawei-p30-pro\">2. Huawei P30 Pro</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":203} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/p30-pro-arora-0.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-203\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Huawei\'s best Android phone ever</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date:&nbsp;</strong>March 2019 |&nbsp;<strong>Weight:&nbsp;</strong>192g |&nbsp;<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>158 x 73.4 x 8.4mm |&nbsp;<strong>OS:&nbsp;</strong>Android 9 |&nbsp;<strong>Screen size:&nbsp;</strong>6.47-inch |&nbsp;<strong>CPU:&nbsp;</strong>Kirin 980 |&nbsp;<strong>RAM:&nbsp;</strong>8GB |&nbsp;<strong>Storage:&nbsp;</strong>128/256/512GB |&nbsp;<strong>Battery:&nbsp;</strong>4,200mAh |&nbsp;<strong>Rear camera:&nbsp;</strong>40MP + 20MP + 8MP + ToF |&nbsp;<strong>Front camera:&nbsp;</strong>32MP</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fantastic cameras Eye-catching design Display \'only\' Full HDEMUI lacks polish</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Huawei P30 Pro could be the best Android phone we\'ve used when it comes to photography. Its 5x and 10x zoom capabilities are staggeringly good. It also performs fantastically well in low light.Advertisement</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For those who really want to get up close to their subject, the P30 Pro also offers a 50x digital zoom, and although quality is reduced it\'s still impressive.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You also get plenty of power under the hood, an in-display fingerprint scanner, premium design and wireless charging with the ability to wireless charge other devices from the back of the P30 Pro.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s a top, top Android phone and only narrowly misses out on top spot due to the Galaxy S10 Plus\' overall slicker and more rounded smartphone experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"3-samsung-galaxy-s10\">3. Samsung Galaxy S10</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":204} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/61YVqHdFRxL._SX569_.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-204\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A top Android phone, overshadowed by its big brother</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date:&nbsp;</strong>March 2019 |&nbsp;<strong>Weight:&nbsp;</strong>157g |&nbsp;<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>149.9 x 70.4 x 7.8mm |&nbsp;<strong>OS:&nbsp;</strong>Android 9 |&nbsp;<strong>Screen size:&nbsp;</strong>6.1-inch |&nbsp;<strong>Resolution:&nbsp;</strong>1440 x 3040 |&nbsp;<strong>CPU:&nbsp;</strong>Snapdragon 855 / Exynos 9820 |&nbsp;<strong>RAM:&nbsp;</strong>8GB |&nbsp;<strong>Storage:&nbsp;</strong>128/512GB |&nbsp;<strong>Battery:&nbsp;</strong>3,400mAh |&nbsp;<strong>Rear camera:&nbsp;</strong>12MP + 12MP + 16MP |&nbsp;<strong>Front camera:&nbsp;</strong>10MP</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Great screen-to-body ratioWireless PowerShare perkS10 Plus is betterBixby button not needed</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s close at the top, with Huawei snapping at Samsung\'s heels it\'s never been tougher for the South Korean firm, but the Galaxy S10 still manages to muscle its way into number three spot.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bigger S10 Plus is by far Samsung\'s best phone, but the standard S10 backs almost all the same top-end features into a more compact form factor and slightly lower price tag (but still steep).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy S10 gets proper under-the-hood upgrades. You’ll like all of these powerful features, while your friends will like the new Wireless PowerShare perk – it helps them out more than you.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"4-huawei-mate-20-pro\">4. Huawei Mate 20 Pro</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":205} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/huawei-mate-20-proheader.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-205\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A power-house of an Android phone</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date:&nbsp;</strong>November 2018 |&nbsp;<strong>Weight:&nbsp;</strong>189g |&nbsp;<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>157.8 x 72.3 x 8.6mm |&nbsp;<strong>OS:&nbsp;</strong>Android 9 |&nbsp;<strong>Screen size:&nbsp;</strong>6.39-inch |&nbsp;<strong>Resolution:&nbsp;</strong>1440 x 3120 |&nbsp;<strong>CPU:&nbsp;</strong>Kirin 980 |&nbsp;<strong>RAM:&nbsp;</strong>8GB |&nbsp;<strong>Storage:&nbsp;</strong>256GB |&nbsp;<strong>Battery:&nbsp;</strong>4200mAh |&nbsp;<strong>Rear camera:&nbsp;</strong>40MP + 20MP + 8MP |&nbsp;<strong>Front camera:&nbsp;</strong>24MP</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In-screen fingerprint scannerGreat triple camerasThe UI needs refinementHigh price</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Huawei Mate 20 Pro offers up a heady mix of design, power and performance with a party piece in the form of an in-display fingerprint scanner thrown in too.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Mate 20 Pro packs a huge 6.39-inch display giving you a lots of space for gaming and movies, and its QHD resolution and HDR10 support ensures everything looks great.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It also comes with three rear cameras, nabbing the excellent 40MP wide-angle and 8MP telephoto lenses from the P20 Pro - but the third sensor is new. It\'s an ultra-wide 16MP snapper allowing you to cram even more of your surroundings into each shot.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Mate 20 Pro is a full-featured phone for a full-featured price - it even has a few tricks you won’t see elsewhere, and more powerful specs than most of its competitors.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 id=\"5-samsung-galaxy-note-9\">5. Samsung Galaxy Note 9</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":206} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Samsung-Galaxy-Note-9-Official-600x600.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-206\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the highest-spec phones on the market</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Release date:&nbsp;</strong>August 2018 |&nbsp;<strong>Weight:&nbsp;</strong>205g |&nbsp;<strong>Dimensions:&nbsp;</strong>162 x 76.4 x 9mm |&nbsp;<strong>OS:&nbsp;</strong>Android 8.1 |&nbsp;<strong>Screen size:&nbsp;</strong>6.4-inch |&nbsp;<strong>Resolution:&nbsp;</strong>2960×1440 |&nbsp;<strong>CPU:&nbsp;</strong>Exynos 9810 |&nbsp;<strong>RAM:&nbsp;</strong>6/8GB |&nbsp;<strong>Storage:&nbsp;</strong>128/512GB (up to 1TB with card) |&nbsp;<strong>Battery:&nbsp;</strong>4,000mAh |&nbsp;<strong>Rear camera:&nbsp;</strong>12MP + 12MP |&nbsp;<strong>Front camera:&nbsp;</strong>8MP<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://amazon.com/Samsung-Factory-Unlocked-Warranty-Lavender/dp/B07H8PXT7K?psc=1&amp;SubscriptionId=AKIAIPHVZTVH6LZ5BFZA&amp;tag=hawk-future-20&amp;linkCode=xm2&amp;camp=2025&amp;creative=165953&amp;creativeASIN=B07H8PXT7K&amp;ascsubtag=trd-custom-tracking-20\" target=\"_blank\"><strong> </strong></a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Much better batteryImproved S PenHefty device to holdMostly iterative upgrades</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The South Korean features again with Galaxy Note 9 in at five in our best Android phones lists.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Galaxy Note 9 boasts a huge screen and a huge amount of power under the hood, plus there\'s the iconic S Pen stylus which slides into the body of the phone for safe keeping.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It means the Note 9 offers a huge array of productivity functions few phones can compete with, but the overall package isn\'t quite as finessed as the Galaxy S10 Plus - not to mention its high price tag.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For power users who want a phone that will doing pretty much anything they ask of it, the Galaxy Note 9 is a top choice.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '5 best Android phones 2019', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '201-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-06-26 14:09:35', '2019-06-26 11:09:35', '', 201, 'http://localhost/wordpress/2019/06/26/201-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
